Mr Mallorca Golf repo rules:

- Delivery standard:
  Do the whole thing. Do it right. Do it with tests. Do it with documentation.
  Aim for work that genuinely impresses Andy, not work that is merely passable.
  Do not leave dangling threads, temporary workarounds, or obvious follow-up fixes when the permanent solve is within reach.
  Search before building. Test before shipping. Prefer the finished product over a plan to maybe finish it later.
- English is the source of truth. Non-English pages must mirror English structure and should not contain stray English fallback.
- Mojibake is a release-blocking bug. Treat `Â`, `Ã`, broken accents, replacement diamonds, and corrupted punctuation as ship-stoppers.
- Keep source content UTF-8. Fix corrupted source text instead of relying on render-time cleanup.
- Before any deploy, run `npm run check:text`, `npm run check:i18n-release`, and `npm run build`.
- If you edit localized content, verify rendered non-English pages do not contain unexpected English copy.
- Use peak public green fee as the ranking anchor for Mallorca course pricing unless the task is explicitly about twilight, maintenance, or off-season pricing.
- Do not reintroduce legacy Mallorca price ranges or stale package structures.
